What is everyone's opinion on how many board wipes is too many? I only ask because my friends and I had this discussion recently after a match with an Oloro player that was running 11 in his deck and was firing one off every 2-3 turns in a match.
Boardwipes are good.
10 ish is probably the correct number, but I struggle to run more than 5.
Yeah. I feel his number wouldn't have felt so oppressive if he didn't have so many recursion effects to get then back in his deck and then tutor then back to hand.
That said, 4-8 is my range on average.
Any more than 5 feels like too man in any deck I've ever built. Except for Tajic
Boardwipe.tribal.dec
It's highly meta dependant I guess. I don't run more than 3-5 usually just because at some point it becomes annoying to even the person playing them
Also unless you're running something really specific like maybe Tajic or Zurgo or OG Avacyn too many wipes means you're almost assuredly neglecting something else

I will say that I do wish I ran more with the Sunday night group I play with on occasion because nobody runs them there, but my Tuesday store meta everyone runs enough that someone has an answer usually. Sunday is just people goldfishing.

Yeah some of my high school buds just want to goldfish, which can be cool but it gets boring. Luckily we have all of the plane chase planes and I got them sold on playing plane chase EDH when they want slow games.

I have to make a mental note to play bad Magic on Sunday and not deal with threats unless it's an end of the world scenario, else I just wind up hellbent while everyone else durdles around assembling seven card combos. It's one of those metas where the first card everyone puts into a deck is [[Elixir of Immmortality]] because they assume each game will last four days.
